onor of the great 10th-century law-giving Welsh king. The name may also arise from the Breton personal name <i>Houuel</i>, <i>Huwel</i>, <i>Huwal</i>, <i>Howael</i>, cognate with the Welsh name. Bretons were especially numerous in the eastern counties of England. See   Powell  .","English: perhaps from a Middle English personal name <i>Huwel</i> (spelled <i>Howel</i>), a shortening of <i>Huwelot</i> or <i>Huelin</i> (see   Hewlett   and   Huling  ), both pet forms of Middle English <i>Huw</i> (see   Hugh  ).","English: habitational name from Howell (Lincolnshire), from an uncertain initial element + Old English <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’."],"variants":[{"name":"Howle","meanings":["English and Welsh:","variant of   Howell  .","variant of   Hole  ."]},{"name":"Howells","meanings":["English and Welsh (Glamorgan): variant of   Howell  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent English <i>-s</i>.","English: perhaps occasionally a nickname for someone who was fearless, from Middle English <i>houe</i>, <i>houwe</i> ‘anxiety, fear’ (Old English <i>hogu</i> or <i>hoga</i>) + <i>les</i> ‘less’. If this has survived as a modern surname, its pronunciation has been influenced by that of the name in 1 above.","English: variant of   Holes  ."]},{"name":"Powell","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>ap Hywel</i> ‘son of <i>Hywel</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘eminent’ (see   Howell  ).","Irish: mainly of Welsh origin as in 1 above, but sometimes a surname adopted as equivalent of Gaelic <b>Mac Giolla Phóil</b> ‘son of the servant of Saint Paul’ (see   Guilfoyle  ).","English: variant of   Paul   or   Poole  ."]}]},{"name":"Mallt","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Maud</b> , a common name in the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Fwyall","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Fyall in Fife."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mallt Fwyall Howell was born in 1528, in Wales, her father, Sir Howel Y Fwyall, was 48 and her mother, Mrs. Howel Y. Fwyall, was 38. She married John Powel “Lord of Maermawr” Madog about 1549, in Wales. They were the parents of at least 5 sons. She died in 1585, in Wales, South Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1528–1585":"1528–1585","1525–1560":"1525–1560","1543–Male":"1543–Surnud","1550–1639":"1550–1639","1552–Male":"1552–Surnud","1554–Male":"1554–Surnud","1555–Male":"1555–Surnud","1480–1536":"1480–1536","1490–Female":"1490–Surnud","1550":"1550","1560":"1560","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1536":"1536","1525":"1525","abt 1555":"umbes 1555","about 1549":"umbes 1549","1555":"1555","1543":"1543","1554":"1554","1552":"1552","1585":"1585","about 1554":"umbes 1554","1639":"1639","1528":"1528","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","England":"England","Wales England":"Wales, South Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Breconshire, Wales":"Breconshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1528–1585":"1528–1585","1525–1560":"1525–1560","1543–Male":"1543–Kuollut","1550–1639":"1550–1639","1552–Male":"1552–Kuollut","1554–Male":"1554–Kuollut","1555–Male":"1555–Kuollut","1480–1536":"1480–1536","1490–Female":"1490–Kuollut","1550":"1550","1560":"1560","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1536":"1536","1525":"1525","abt 1555":"noin 1555","about 1549":"noin 1549","1555":"1555","1543":"1543","1554":"1554","1552":"1552","1585":"1585","about 1554":"noin 1554","1639":"1639","1528":"1528","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales","England":"England","Wales England":"Wales, South Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Breconshire, Wales":"Breconshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1528–1585":"1528–1585","1525–1560":"1525–1560","1543–Male":"1543–Décédé","1550–1639":"1550–1639","1552–Male":"1552–Décédé","1554–Male":"1554–Décédé","1555–Male":"1555–Décédé","1480–1536":"1